snippet.textDisplay: There was a point there in the 50th minute or so where it struck me how amazing this team is... theres been so much difficulty in the past 11 years of my support of lfc— that I sort of created a sense of super engaged yet protectedly detached support, especially as we reached these extreme heights the past year. after the brutal night in madrid, and when man city pulled away with it last season, I kind of had to reign back the emotional involvement in the team, because i was so devastated that it really impacted me in a negative way. Even the champions league win, i felt i couldnt enjoy it to the fullest extent... a vexing and disconcerting feeling..,but at some point around the 50th minute, the level of performance, and the cohesion amongst the lads, even the way the commentators waxed poetic about our side... i was completely disarmed and started crying... unexpectedly... then we went on to score three more goals... and the entire time i was rapt with glee as I finally felt safe in knowing that we are the greatest team in the world, and one of the greatest football teams of all time... and of course the greatest football club in history... ynwa... i love you and the other redmen so much. you make me feel connected to the scouse heartbeat of this beautiful club. thank you
